name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: fs.s3a.attempts.maximum
description: How many times we should retry commands on transient errors.

name: ipc.[port_number].weighted-cost.response
description:
The weight multiplier to apply to the time spent in the
    RESPONSE phase which do not involve holding a lock.
    See org.apache.hadoop.ipc.ProcessingDetails.Timing for more details on
    this phase. This property applies to WeightedTimeCostProvider.

name: mapreduce.reduce.shuffle.connect.timeout
description:
Expert: The maximum amount of time (in milli seconds) reduce
  task spends in trying to connect to a remote node for getting map output.

name: dfs.datanode.ec.reconstruction.threads
description:
Number of threads used by the Datanode for background
    reconstruction work.

name: dfs.client.retry.interval-ms.get-last-block-length
description:
Retry interval in milliseconds to wait between retries in getting
    block lengths from the datanodes.

name: ha.health-monitor.rpc-timeout.ms
description: Timeout for the actual monitorHealth() calls.

name: ha.health-monitor.rpc.connect.max.retries
description:
The number of retries on connect error when establishing RPC proxy
    connection to NameNode, used for monitorHealth() calls.

name: dfs.datanode.ec.reconstruct.write.bandwidthPerSec
description:
Specifies the maximum amount of bandwidth that the EC reconstruction can utilize for writing.
      When the bandwidth value is zero, there is no limit.
